<concept id="querying_and_transactions"> 
  <title>Queries and Indexes with Transactions</title> 
  <prolog><metadata><keywords><keyword>gemfire queries
			 transactions</keyword><keyword>gemfire indexes
			 transactions</keyword></keywords></metadata>
  </prolog> 
  <conbody> 
	 <section id="section_881D2FF6761B4D689DDB46C650E2A2E1">
		<p>Queries and indexes reflect the cache and ignore the changes made by
		  ongoing transactions. If you do a query from inside a transaction, the query
		  does not reflect the changes you made inside that transaction. 
		</p>
	 </section> 
  </conbody> 
</concept> 
